{"TopicId":139294,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"And they all fell down! (flags that is)","CreatedByName":"Brainlord Mesomorph","CreatedById":110905,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-08T11:09:21Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Brainlord Mesomorph","CreatedById":110905,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-08T11:09:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1.1.2 Everywhere I look, all my flags are falling over.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-08T11:09:40Z\u0022 title=\u002205/08/2016 11:09  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 8, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Brainlord Mesomorph\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"algeo","CreatedById":147723,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-08T11:53:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIsn\u0027t that realistic? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wjolcz","CreatedById":39636,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-08T12:34:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen perhaps report it as a bug instead of posting a thread here?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Brainlord Mesomorph","CreatedById":110905,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-08T12:40:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just stopped looking.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd sorry, I file, and fix bug reports, 60\u00A0hours a week.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe closest thing you\u0027ll get out me on a Sunday morning is a snarky comment \u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ferrer","CreatedById":161724,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-08T14:28:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI had this issue on the Mun a few days ago, and not too long before that I had an exploding flag as well. I just took it as reasonably normal behaviour for KSP\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-08T16:00:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222568686\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022139294\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462708402\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022147723\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022algeo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, algeo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIsn\u0027t that realistic? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope.\u00A0 Not in a vacuum.\u00A0 There is no wind to push it over, no wind or water to erode the land around it.\u00A0 Barring a perfect meteor strike, it should stay there forever.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith the exception of Apollo 11, all the Moon\u0027s flags are still standing (but sun-bleached and pure white), and Apollo 11\u0027s flag was knocked over by the LEM ascent because they put it too close.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"algeo","CreatedById":147723,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-08T16:08:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222569063\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022139294\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462723225\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110959\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alshain\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Alshain said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope.\u00A0 Not in a vacuum.\u00A0 There is no wind to push it over, no wind or water to erode the land around it.\u00A0 Barring a perfect meteor strike, it should stay there forever.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith the exception of Apollo 11, all the Moon\u0027s flags are still standing (but sun-bleached and pure white), and Apollo 11\u0027s flag was knocked over by the LEM ascent because they put it too close.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell he didn\u0027t specify that it was on the m\u00FCn. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alshain","CreatedById":110959,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-08T16:16:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222569076\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022139294\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462723733\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022147723\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022algeo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, algeo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell he didn\u0027t specify that it was on the m\u00FCn. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah but there are 4 planets/moons with atmosphere and 11 without, so odds are if \u0027everywhere he looks\u0027 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-09T18:59:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYup. \u00A0 Me too, they just fall over gently and rock about a bit. \u00A0At least they stay there - unless they are on a slope then\u00A0they can just roll to the bottom and settle there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt first I thought it was flags planted\u00A0pre 1.1, but I had it happen to new ones too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Brotoro","CreatedById":57674,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-10T05:24:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222568737\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022139294\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462710847\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002239636\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Veeltch\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn May 8, 2016 at 6:34 AM, Veeltch said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen perhaps report it as a bug instead of posting a thread here?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow could Squad possibly not know this by now? It\u0027s the first thing I noticed after opening an old save in 1.1 (which other people had been playing for weeks before me).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PrestonM","CreatedById":167184,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-29T07:38:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI took it as a challenge, so I built a probe with a downward facing grabber unit and two sets of landing struts, one higher than the other. I landed near the flag, scooted over it with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E, and retracted the lower set of legs to drop the grabber down. It actually worked, I just had to use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E to push the ship down to get it to grab the flag. Lifted off and brought it home to the space center as a souvenir!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Astrofox","CreatedById":135785,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-29T20:48:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222568903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022139294\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462717705\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161724\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ferrer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/8/2016 at 10:28 AM, ferrer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nexploding flag\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWait. What?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}